## 1. What this gate decides

Implementation may open in order, **P0 first** (ICP-DELETE-LEAF API repair) before any OpenChatZD
work: the engine must support host-supplied `record_id` and host-authorized Phase C finalization first.

---

## 2. Decisions

**D1 — Scope: per-user `user` canister PII only.** Shared-canister PII out of scope, disclosed plainly
(§5); build on `RESIDUAL_TRUST_STATEMENT.md:40-50`.

**D2 — Erasure & orchestration (firm, frontend-orchestrated, delete-last):**
> confirmation → **Phase A** (tombstone, set `certified_data`, returns pending receipt-id, takes
> finalization lock — `lib.rs:112-127`) → **Phase B** (ingress query; `data_certificate()` is
> query-only — `README.md:34-37`, `lib.rs:133-145`, `finalization.rs:112-138`) → **Phase C**
> (host-authorized finalize) → **store** in receipts canister → **display + JSON download / copy
> id+token** → **then** `deleteCurrentUser` → `uninstall_code` (`delete_users.rs:68-77`).

**D3 — Verification profile: V1–V3 archival; V4 N/A by design.**

**D4 — Durable store: dedicated receipts canister** + best-effort user export/download
(`export.rs:16-20`). Not `user_index` blobs, not return-only.

**D5 — User-facing receipt display/download is a hard requirement.** Receipt screen (summary, bounded
scope, residual disclosure, JSON download, copy id+token) before the delete pipeline runs. Conventions
exist (`ConfirmDeleteAccount.svelte:27-43`, `utils/blob.ts:1-5`). "Unconditional" = not opt-in.

**D6 — Phase C authorization repair (additive).** Default `finalize_receipt` keeps controller-only
(`finalization.rs:145-180`). Add non-public `finalize_receipt_after_host_authorization(...)` (not
`authorized: bool`): host authorizes first; finalizes only the current pending receipt; fails on
receipt-id mismatch. OpenChatZD user canister exposes an owner-guarded wrapper (`set_bio.rs:1-14`).

**D7 — Host-supplied `record_id` repair (additive).** Engine derives from `caller()`
(`engine.rs:81-84`); trait has no hook (`trait_def.rs:46-58`). Add
`execute_deletion_with_record_id(...)`, keep caller-derived `execute_deletion`. OpenChatZD supplies a
stable, non-raw, domain-tagged reference, not `caller()`.

**D8 — Phase A is the point of no return.** Enforced by the finalization lock (`lib.rs:119-121`,
`engine.rs:124-130`). No rollback in v1. (a) On B/C/storage failure → blocking retry/recovery, no
pipeline trigger, no restoration of normal use; (b) no uninstall until storage confirmed (O8);
(c) flow resumable/idempotent; (d) **admin recovery/resume procedure — owned by P3** (see §6).

