## 6. Implementation packet sequence

**P0 — ICP-DELETE-LEAF API repair (first).** Additive `execute_deletion_with_record_id` +
`finalize_receipt_after_host_authorization`; confirm MemoryId range (O6); default paths unchanged.
*Validation:* unit tests; DaffyDefs regression; **adversarial security review of the host-auth path**;
full release gate (Arweave, RELEASES linter, tag). See `P0_BuildPacket_Brief.md`.

**P1 — OpenChatZD user-canister adapter + A/B/C wrappers.** `MKTdDataSource`; owner-guarded A/B/C;
pending/failure behaviour (D8); set `base_memory_id` after O6 + `chat_events`; **expose a
pending-finalization-state query** for P3's recovery detection. *Validation:* round-trip; guard
coverage; lock-blocks-mutation.

**P2 — Dedicated receipts canister.** `store_finalized_receipt` / `get_receipt_by_lookup_token` /
`get_receipt_by_id(receipt_id, token)`; hashed identifiers; idempotent. *Validation:* store/retrieve;
idempotency; no-raw-lookup test.

**P3 — Delete-pipeline sequencing guard + recovery.** `deleteCurrentUser`/uninstall fires only after
confirmed storage; no race to `uninstall_code`. **Plus (G amendment):** a minimal admin
recovery/resume procedure for a permanently-stuck post-Phase-A pending-receipt state. *Validation:*
race/ordering test; crash-resumability; **detection of pending-finalization state (via P1's query) and
safe re-entry or administrative resume without triggering uninstall prematurely.**

**P4 — Frontend receipt UX.** Desktop + mobile delete flow → A→B→C/storage → receipt screen (summary,
bounded scope, **residual disclosure — needs O2**, JSON download, copy id/token) → then pipeline;
failure/recovery states. *Validation:* both platforms; failure paths.

**P5 — End-to-end proof run.** Test user → finalized CVDR → stored → displayed/downloaded → uninstall
→ verify V1–V3, V4 documented N/A, residual disclosure shown.

